        <h2 class="section-title">Data Security Concerns</h2>
        <p>Snowflake environments present unique security challenges due to their multi-tenant nature, extensive data sharing capabilities, and role-based access models. Understanding these risks is essential for maintaining robust data protection.</p>
        
        <div class="concerns-grid">
            <div class="concern-card">
                <h4>Over-Permissioned Roles</h4>
                <p>Complex role hierarchies can lead to excessive data access permissions.</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Inherited permissions from multiple roles</li>
                    <li>Broad database and schema access</li>
                    <li>Service accounts with admin privileges</li>
                    <li>Temporary access that becomes permanent</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            
            <div class="concern-card">
                <h4>Data Sharing Risks</h4>
                <p>Snowflake's data sharing features can inadvertently expose sensitive information.</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Shared datasets containing PII</li>
                    <li>External data shares without proper governance</li>
                    <li>Customer data in analytics shares</li>
                    <li>Unmonitored cross-account data access</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            
            <div class="concern-card">
                <h4>Data Classification Gaps</h4>
                <p>Rapid data ingestion can outpace classification and governance efforts.</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Untagged sensitive tables and columns</li>
                    <li>Mixed sensitivity levels in datasets</li>
                    <li>External data without classification</li>
                    <li>Historical data lacking proper tags</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
